## Overview

This project documents an end-to-end internal Active Directory penetration test against a lab domain (`ArsenalDomain.com`) that I designed, built, and then compromised. The lab was deliberately seeded with realistic misconfigurations — including decoy "loot" files — to practise distinguishing genuine attack paths from red herrings.

**Objective:** Starting from a single low-privilege domain user credential, escalate to Domain Admin and capture a designated high-value account (`a-mkitavi`).

**Outcome:** Full domain compromise. Extracted all 38 credential hashes via DCSync, obtained an interactive shell on the Domain Controller, and demonstrated pass-the-hash against the target account.

