## Key Takeaway

The deliberately-planted "loot" — a credential file and a service-account script — led nowhere. Full domain compromise came instead from quiet enumeration and a single reused password on a privileged account. That mirrors real engagements far more than any capture-the-flag breadcrumb: **the loudest finding is rarely the one that owns the domain, and credential hygiene on privileged accounts is the control that matters most.**

